.pageContent
  = render "layouts/alerts"

  %p
    To import an assignment, upload a .csv file with the following format. These fields <b> MUST </b> be in the specified order. Note the following:
    %ul
      %li You may include additional information in the extra columns, but that content will be ignored.
      %li If the Assignment Type does not match one that is currently in the course, you will be allowed to select or create a new one.
      %li
        The Due Date must be in the following format:
        %span.italic= "mm/dd/yyyy hh:mm:ss (e.g. 01/01/2017 15:10:11)"
        %br If the format of the due date cannot be parsed, you will be allowed to change it.

  %hr

    %p
      Columns should be in the following order:
      %br Assignment Name, Assignment Type Name, Point Total, Description, Due Date
      .bold= link_to "Download Sample File", assignments_importer_download_path(:csv, format: "csv")

    = form_tag(action: :upload, importer_provider_id: :csv, multipart: true) do
      = file_field_tag "file"

      .submit-buttons
        .right
          = active_course_submit_tag "Import", class: "button"
